        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/10–2545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Syria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Porter</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-25">October 25,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received October 25—4:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. At press conference yesterday Premier stated: “Reestablishment of our
                    relations with France conditional upon three points: first, the withdrawal of
                    troops; second, transfer to us of remaining powers and attributes; third,
                    settlement question diplomatic representation on normal basis.” Explaining last
                    point Premier said Syria could not tolerate presence of French Delegate General
                    and that French, like other powers, should be represented here by Minister.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Porter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
